The Grammy-award winner's successes included The Supremes' single Baby Love and Phil Collins' Two Hearts. Producer Brandon Williams wrote: "Thank you for all you did.You made this place better."  Detroit-born Lamont, a married dad of three, was one third of a song-writing team with the Holland brothers, Brian and Eddie. Their hits included Reach Out I'll Be There and Baby I Need Your Loving. No cause of death has been revealed. 